<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1096,1442]" box="[151,278,1096,1122]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Comments</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1096,1442]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
The “triconcave” prosternum of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[581,765,1136,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouchardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[581,765,1136,1161]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scol. bouchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[774,868,1135,1161]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[774,868,1135,1161]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[926,1131,1136,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difficillimus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[926,1131,1136,1161]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scol. difficillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1139,1233,1135,1161]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1139,1233,1135,1161]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique among the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kawanabe &amp; Miyatake" authorityYear="1996" box="[194,382,1176,1202]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xylographellini">Xylographellini</taxonomicName>
, although that is a character not easy to observe (the prosternum itself is very short in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Blair" authorityYear="1928" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scolytocis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The “triconcave” prosternum is here defined as the prosternum with a slightly concave disc, with either lateral side concave but in different plane than the disc, appearing triconcave in frontal view. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouchardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scolytocis bouchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[277,371,1295,1321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[277,371,1295,1321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[613,818,1296,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difficillimus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[613,818,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scol. difficillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[825,919,1295,1321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[825,919,1295,1321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(from 
<collectingCountry box="[1000,1103,1296,1322]" name="Ecuador" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1096,1442]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Specimens of both 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[423,608,1336,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouchardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[423,608,1336,1361]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scol. bouchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[615,708,1335,1361]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[615,708,1335,1361]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[766,971,1336,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difficillimus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[766,971,1336,1361]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scol. difficillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[978,1071,1335,1361]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[978,1071,1335,1361]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
may be confused with the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[277,392,1376,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lawrencei">
<emphasis box="[277,392,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">lawrencei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, mainly with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes-Andrade, 2008" authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[628,806,1376,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lawrencei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[628,806,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scol. lawrencei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[813,906,1375,1402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,899,1375,1401]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes-Andrade" authorityYear="2008" box="[1241,1360,1376,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Ciidae" genus="Scolytocis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouchardi">
<emphasis box="[1241,1360,1376,1401]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">bouchardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group have larger hindwings and smaller male genitalia.
</paragraph>
